cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE

The paper focuses on the challenges faced by deep learning in exploiting superficial statistics and dataset bias, and proposes a test to evaluate abstract reasoning over visual data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates a range of deep learning architectures, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
